{"id":"mini-test-26-futur-i","title":"Mini Test 26: Futur I","description":"Practice Futur I (werden + infinitive) for predictions and intentions","duration":12,"category":"grammar","focus":"Verbs","questions":[{"id":"q1","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Morgen ___ ich nach Berlin fahren.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"werde"},{"id":"b","text":"werden"},{"id":"c","text":"wird"},{"id":"d","text":"würde"}],"correctAnswerId":"a","explanation":"Futur I: ich werde + infinitive","explanationDetail":"Futur I: werden (conjugated) + infinitive at end. Ich werde fahren.","tags":["verbs","futur"]},{"id":"q2","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Er ___ das Buch lesen.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"werde"},{"id":"b","text":"werden"},{"id":"c","text":"wird"},{"id":"d","text":"werdet"}],"correctAnswerId":"c","explanation":"Futur I: er wird lesen","explanationDetail":"Er/sie/es → wird. Er wird das Buch lesen.","tags":["verbs","futur"]},{"id":"q3","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Wir ___ nächstes Jahr umziehen.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"werde"},{"id":"b","text":"werden"},{"id":"c","text":"wird"},{"id":"d","text":"werdet"}],"correctAnswerId":"b","explanation":"Futur I: wir werden","explanationDetail":"Wir → werden. Wir werden umziehen.","tags":["verbs","futur"]},{"id":"q4","type":"multiple-choice","text":"___ du morgen kommen?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Wirst"},{"id":"b","text":"Werden"},{"id":"c","text":"Wird"},{"id":"d","text":"Werde"}],"correctAnswerId":"a","explanation":"Futur I: Wirst du kommen?","explanationDetail":"Du → wirst. Verb in position 2 in questions.","tags":["verbs","futur"]},{"id":"q5","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Sie ___ sicher gewinnen.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"werde"},{"id":"b","text":"werden"},{"id":"c","text":"wird"},{"id":"d","text":"werdet"}],"correctAnswerId":"c","explanation":"Sie (she) → wird","explanationDetail":"Sie (3rd person singular) → wird. Sie wird gewinnen.","tags":["verbs","futur"]},{"id":"q6","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Ihr ___ die Prüfung bestehen.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"werde"},{"id":"b","text":"werden"},{"id":"c","text":"wird"},{"id":"d","text":"werdet"}],"correctAnswerId":"d","explanation":"Futur I: ihr werdet","explanationDetail":"Ihr → werdet. Ihr werdet bestehen.","tags":["verbs","futur"]},{"id":"q7","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Es ___ morgen regnen.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"werde"},{"id":"b","text":"werden"},{"id":"c","text":"wird"},{"id":"d","text":"werdet"}],"correctAnswerId":"c","explanation":"Es → wird (weather)","explanationDetail":"Es wird regnen (it will rain). Prediction.","tags":["verbs","futur"]},{"id":"q8","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Die Kinder ___ im Park spielen.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"werde"},{"id":"b","text":"werden"},{"id":"c","text":"wird"},{"id":"d","text":"werdet"}],"correctAnswerId":"b","explanation":"Plural → werden","explanationDetail":"Die Kinder (plural) → werden. Sie werden spielen.","tags":["verbs","futur"]},{"id":"q9","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Ich ___ dir helfen.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"werde"},{"id":"b","text":"werden"},{"id":"c","text":"wird"},{"id":"d","text":"würde"}],"correctAnswerId":"a","explanation":"Ich werde dir helfen (intention)","explanationDetail":"Futur I can express intention. Ich werde dir helfen.","tags":["verbs","futur"]},{"id":"q10","type":"multiple-choice","text":"___ ihr am Samstag kommen?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Werdet"},{"id":"b","text":"Werden"},{"id":"c","text":"Wird"},{"id":"d","text":"Werde"}],"correctAnswerId":"a","explanation":"Werdet ihr kommen?","explanationDetail":"Question: verb first. Werdet ihr am Samstag kommen?","tags":["verbs","futur"]},{"id":"q11","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Nächstes Jahr ___ sie in München wohnen.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"werde"},{"id":"b","text":"werden"},{"id":"c","text":"wird"},{"id":"d","text":"werdet"}],"correctAnswerId":"c","explanation":"Sie (she) wird wohnen","explanationDetail":"Sie wird nächstes Jahr in München wohnen.","tags":["verbs","futur"]},{"id":"q12","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Du ___ das schaffen.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"werde"},{"id":"b","text":"wirst"},{"id":"c","text":"wird"},{"id":"d","text":"werdet"}],"correctAnswerId":"b","explanation":"Du wirst schaffen","explanationDetail":"Du → wirst. Du wirst das schaffen.","tags":["verbs","futur"]},{"id":"q13","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Wir ___ ihn anrufen.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"werde"},{"id":"b","text":"werden"},{"id":"c","text":"wird"},{"id":"d","text":"werdet"}],"correctAnswerId":"b","explanation":"Wir werden anrufen","explanationDetail":"Wir werden ihn anrufen.","tags":["verbs","futur"]},{"id":"q14","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Er ___ sicher pünktlich sein.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"werde"},{"id":"b","text":"werden"},{"id":"c","text":"wird"},{"id":"d","text":"werdet"}],"correctAnswerId":"c","explanation":"Er wird sein (prediction)","explanationDetail":"Er wird pünktlich sein. Prediction with sein.","tags":["verbs","futur"]},{"id":"q15","type":"multiple-choice","text":"Sie (plural) ___ uns besuchen.","options":[{"id":"a","text":"werde"},{"id":"b","text":"werden"},{"id":"c","text":"wird"},{"id":"d","text":"werdet"}],"correctAnswerId":"b","explanation":"Sie (they) werden besuchen","explanationDetail":"Sie (plural) → werden. Sie werden uns besuchen.","tags":["verbs","futur"]}]}